	<p>To prepare the wax positive for the plaster negative, additional wax branches fuse to the fighter to act as a funnel and channel for the eventual flow of melted bronze.<sup>3</sup> To prepare the plaster mold, a cylindrical cage of chicken wire provides structural support around the centered wax and a tarp-like paper temporarily encases the cage to constrain the curing plaster.<sup>4</sup></p>
